You have lot of options to do that. 

**Option 1 : Projections from Spring Data JPA without @Query**

    interface MyProjection{
        String getField1();
        String getField3();
    }
    public interface MyRepository extends JpaRepository&lt;Entity, Integer&gt; {
    
        List&lt;MyProjection&gt; findAll();
    }

**Option 2 : Projections from Spring Data JPA with @Query (quite similar to Option 1)**


    interface MyProjection{
        String getField1();
        String getField3();
    }
    public interface MyRepository extends JpaRepository&lt;Entity, Integer&gt; {
        @Query(&quot;SELECT p FROM Entity p&quot;)
        List&lt;MyProjection&gt; customFindEntity();
    }

**Option 3 : Projections from Spring Data JPA with @Query  without any interface**

    public interface MyRepository extends JpaRepository&lt;Entity, Integer&gt; {
        @Query(&quot;SELECT p.field1,  p.field2 FROM Entity p&quot;)
        List&lt;Object&gt; customFindEntity();
    }


**Option 4 : Projections from Spring Data JPA with @Query an native query (quite similar to Option 2)**


    interface MyProjection{
        String getField1();
        String getField3();
    }
    public interface MyRepository extends JpaRepository&lt;Entity, Integer&gt; {
        @Query(&quot;SELECT field1, field3 FROM Entity p&quot;, nativeQuery = true)
        List&lt;MyProjection&gt; customFindEntity();
    }
**Option 5 : Use Native query and return list of object array**

You have to extract your data from the list of array.


    public interface MyRepository extends JpaRepository&lt;Entity, Integer&gt; {
        @Query(&quot;SELECT field1, field3 FROM Entity p&quot;, nativeQuery = true)
